selenium.dev/downloads
Here you can download Browser drivers, Selenium for Python

Chrome:

https://chromedriver.chromium.org/downloads

Edge:

https://developer.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/tools/webdriver/

Firefox:

https://github.com/mozilla/geckodriver/releases

Safari:(Mac)

https://webkit.org/blog/6900/webdriver-support-in-safari-10/


Setup Selenium WebDriver,
  1)Pycharm--->Project settings
  File->Settings->Project->Python Interpreter->Click + button->Search Selenium->Choose Selenium->Click on Install Package.
  After the Selenium Package installed successfully. Selenium will be displayed in the Python Interpreter list. 
  
  To uninstall select the required package and Click - button in Python the Interpreter.
  
  2)In Terminal window,
  pip install selenium=4.0.0.b4(This will install the mentioned version)
  pip install selenium (This will install the default selenium version)

Install webdriver-manager from settings. then use the statement,
driver=webdriver.Chrome(ChromeDriverManager().install())
This 'll automatically install the chromedriver from the browser.

